  "prompt": "How and how much is announcer Bruce Buffer of MMA Octagon paid?",
  "response": "Bruce Buffer, the famous octagon announcer for the Ultimate Fighting Championship (UFC), is typically compensated through a combination of a base salary and bonuses. While exact figures can vary depending on specific events and negotiations, it has been reported that he earns a range between $50,000 to $100,000 per event he announces. For major pay-per-view events, his pay can be on the higher end of that scale or even more, with some sources suggesting he may earn upwards of $100,000 for significant fights.\n\nBuffer also benefits from bonuses for particularly high-profile events and has been known to have contracts that allow for additional compensation based on pay-per-view sales. Overall, his total earnings can be substantial, especially given the number of events he typically works each year.\n\nAs with any such roles, these figures can vary and may not reflect the most current agreements or arrangements he has, but they give a good general idea of his earning potential within the sport.",
